1
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:05,547
(Yukiya) Kyoko Ise...

2
00:00:06,548 --> 00:00:08,341
erase from that house

3
00:00:11,886 --> 00:00:13,346
(Yukiya) Is it gone?

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:17,684
(Fuyu) No matter how hard I searched, I couldn't find that envelope.

5
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:55,346
(Reo) This is...

6
00:00:57,223 --> 00:00:58,391
 (Erika) At your father-in-law's desk⸺

7
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:01,102
When I thought of returning the fountain pen...

8
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:02,729
(Kyoko) What do you mean?

9
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:05,482
I don't know.

10
00:01:05,565 --> 00:01:07,776
Someone is trying to trick your mother-in-law⸺

11
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:09,944
I can only think that 

12
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:11,988
For Seiichiro⸺

13
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,907
I guess you haven't seen it?

14
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,954
Ha... I can't use it.

15
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:23,458
So what do you think this person said?

16
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:27,504
I told you to be careful

17
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,422
Sorry

18
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:33,343
Because I'm close to you⸺

19
00:01:33,426 --> 00:01:35,178
I'm jealous

20
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:36,679
No.

21
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:40,934
I'm really worried about my mother-in-law...

22
00:01:41,017 --> 00:01:43,394
What are you talking about?

23
00:01:43,478 --> 00:01:47,482
You're worried about the Ise Group, right?

24
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:52,403
Even though you don't care about me

25
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:53,905
That's not my intention...

26
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:57,075
(Kyoko) Well, the group suffers from reputational damage⸺

27
00:01:57,158 --> 00:01:58,952
I'm sorry too.

28
00:01:59,702 --> 00:02:00,703
Yeah…

29
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,789
Please wait a moment

30
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:05,375
Why am I fooling Kyoko?

31
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:10,380
I can understand why the president is worried.

32
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:14,217
But I won't sell Kyoko.

33
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:18,596
Kyoko-san is for me⸺

34
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:21,432
I can't thank you enough for being a benefactor.

35
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,563
that's why…

36
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:35,530
This time, I acted rudely due to my haste.

37
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:37,115
very sorry

38
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,664
I will handle this matter myself.

39
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:47,208
don't worry about the rest

40
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:50,253
I asked for it

41
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:54,632
If Seiichiro is involved, things will get complicated⸺

42
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,509
Don't do anything unnecessary

43
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:59,387
Yeah... I'll handle it properly.

44
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:03,266
Before the dinner, I called you out for something like this⸺

45
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:05,268
I'm sorry

46
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,854
Please enjoy

47
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,690
thank you

48
00:03:37,508 --> 00:03:39,510
‪♪～

49
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:37,568
‪～♪

50
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,366
(Reo) Well, I was surprised.

51
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:44,701
When you receive an email

52
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,452
(Yukiya) That's right.

53
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:50,164
Um...I'm sorry if I suddenly say something like this.

54
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,082
Yeah…

55
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:53,751
I can’t believe it’s Ise-san⸺

56
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:56,170
It has nothing to do with that Ise group, right?

57
00:04:56,254 --> 00:05:00,967
Haha... Ah... Did you find out?

58
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:02,510
yes it's my son

59
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:05,054
Huh? Oh really?

60
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:07,473
Even though I am a son, there are many things.

61
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:12,061
Thank you for taking me in even though I was an orphan.

62
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:14,939
I have nothing but gratitude to my adoptive parents who raised me.

63
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:17,150
That's right

64
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:20,486
(Yukiya) It was against this background that I started “Homohoya”.

65
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:23,072
At that time, I found Marble's homepage.

66
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,408
I was surprised when I saw the photo

67
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:29,996
I think you are doing a great job.

68
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:33,875
I would like to talk to you again slowly.

69
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:36,502
I'm glad you said that.

70
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:37,712
Homoya’s efforts⸺

71
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:40,965
It's really in sync with our philosophy.

72
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:45,553
I'm so happy that someone like that is the son of the Ise family.

73
00:05:46,179 --> 00:05:47,930
I feel like I've met a comrade.

74
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,766
(Yukiya) Welcome.

75
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:52,810
I have friends who understand the management's position.

76
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,020
There weren't many people there, so

77
00:05:54,103 --> 00:05:55,396
That's right, isn't it?

78
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,899
In fact, isn't it difficult just to keep going?

79
00:05:57,982 --> 00:05:59,358
(Yukiya) Really

80
00:05:59,442 --> 00:06:01,903
Mr. Ise, how are you doing in that area?

81
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:06,240
Ah... I'm sorry about the money... Huh?

82
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,951
No, no, that's not the case.

83
00:06:09,535 --> 00:06:12,830
Even after I entered society, I couldn't rely on my parents.

84
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:17,752
I work exclusively on bicycles, and I use the money I work every month.

85
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:19,712
Is that so?

86
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:23,174
Ah... that's amazing, I already have high aspirations.

87
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:26,052
But isn't it difficult? That's it

88
00:06:26,886 --> 00:06:28,221
It's hard

89
00:06:28,888 --> 00:06:30,890
I've always done it my own way⸺

90
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:32,391
There is no pressure

91
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:35,937
What is Mr. Satake doing about that?

92
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:39,816
Ah, I am... Please wait a moment.

93
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:43,820
Do you know this?

94
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:46,781
I also met Kyoko at the presentation.

95
00:06:46,864 --> 00:06:49,909
Oh I know, I know

96
00:06:49,992 --> 00:06:53,287
Even though I know, I'm really not good at things like this⸺

97
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,956
I have never participated

98
00:06:55,039 --> 00:06:57,875
Is that so? That's surprising

99
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,920
I just can't muster up the courage to go alone.

100
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:03,923
Alright, let's participate together next time.

101
00:07:04,006 --> 00:07:05,341
Is it true?

102
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,593
Well, I'm kind of sorry.

103
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:10,471
That's outrageous, Kyoko must be there too.

104
00:07:13,015 --> 00:07:15,810
-(Yukiya) Ah, but Satake-san-(Reo) Yes.

105
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:19,355
Could you please keep this a secret from my mother?

106
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,734
I'm worried

107
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:26,863
If you knew I was having money troubles⸺

108
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:29,240
My mother doesn't sit still.

109
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:34,036
I've been treated really well, so

110
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:05,485
(Seiichiro/Masayuki from childhood) ♪ Happy Birthday

111
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:08,738
♪ Happy birthday

112
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:13,701
♪ Happy birthday to you

113
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:16,162
- (Seiichiro) Congratulations - (Kyoko) Thank you

114
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,457
(sound of breathing)

115
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,752
applause)

116
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:25,296
happy

117
00:08:26,297 --> 00:08:27,423
(Seiichiro) Looks delicious.

118
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,342
(Masayuki) Mom, this is a present.

119
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:32,303
(Kyoko) Wow! thank you

120
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:35,139
Aah! When did you buy it?

121
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,225
- (Seiichiro) Haha... - (Kyoko) I'm happy.

122
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:38,768
(Yukiya from childhood) Congratulations

123
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:43,523
Fuyu-san

124
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:46,234
Can you cut a cake for 3 people?

125
00:08:46,317 --> 00:08:48,236
-(Fuyu) Huh? -(Kyoko) Hehe...

126
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:51,781
I'm tired from partying all day long⸺

127
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,033
I want to spend time with my family without getting wet.

128
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:56,911
(Fuyu) Is it for 3 people?

129
00:08:58,579 --> 00:08:59,956
(Kyoko) Okay? you

130
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:02,124
Do whatever you like

131
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,210
(Kyoko)...So...

132
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:07,171
For 3 people, please

133
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:29,527
(Reporter) Regarding balancing childcare and work⸺

134
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,195
What do you think?

135
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:36,200
Of course, balancing childcare and work is never easy.

136
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:41,038
She still cries at night, so I'm being woken up every hour.

137
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:43,791
I'm already sleep deprived every day (shutter sound)

138
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,545
I can't help but think it's cute though

139
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:51,132
But I don't have any time for myself.

140
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:52,300
Much less⸺

141
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:56,304
Regarding taking on such a responsible position⸺

142
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:58,639
I was worried a lot

143
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:01,642
I cannot accept it with a half-hearted attitude.

144
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:05,271
But the father of the Ise Group⸺

145
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:08,691
Encouraged by Seiichiro Ise's words⸺

146
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,693
This is how I accepted it.

147
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:11,944
(Reporter) Huh...

148
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:13,988
That's a very cool idea

149
00:10:14,071 --> 00:10:15,823
(Erika) Ah, thank you very much.

150
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:17,867
- (Reporter) Thank you - (Erika) Yes.

151
00:10:22,371 --> 00:10:25,249
(Reo) Look, there's an article about Erika.

152
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,544
(Kyoko) Ah...

153
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:30,796
(Reo) That’s amazing.

154
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:33,883
To Marble's homepage⸺

155
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:36,886
I wonder if Erika-san can give me some supportive comments or something?

156
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:41,724
There are quite a few people around me who admire Erika.

157
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:44,226
From Kyoko to Erika⸺

158
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,854
Isn't it possible for you to ask me something?

159
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:50,691
Ah, no, it's a bad thing⸺

160
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:53,694
I wish I could just consult with you.

161
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:55,321
Both us and Kyoko-san⸺

162
00:10:55,404 --> 00:10:58,491
Thanks to Erika, I'm able to do what I do now.

163
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,534
I don't like it

164
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,123
Hehe...

165
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,251
I don't know

166
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:12,421
She says things like this in public⸺

167
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,840
I don't do it at home anymore.

168
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:17,343
almost child abandonment

169
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:20,471
Well, when she gave up⸺

170
00:11:20,554 --> 00:11:23,974
I'm at home, and I also have a helper⸺

171
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:26,644
I don't have any problems though.

172
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:35,027
But what does it mean to admire her?

173
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:39,990
Your friend doesn't really care about people either.

174
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:45,996
Ah...but no comment at all?

175
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:49,041
If you want it, I'll ask it for you.

176
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:52,837
I wouldn't say no to something like that.

177
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,548
But that's it, isn't it?

178
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,883
I'm not talking about Satoshi-kun though.

179
00:11:57,967 --> 00:12:02,304
What if her true appearance became known to the world⸺

180
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:06,016
Isn't the survival of Marble in jeopardy?

181
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,645
An organization that does charity work⸺

182
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:14,150
When I found out that I was hanging out with someone like child abandonment.

183
00:12:15,609 --> 00:12:17,194
I agree

184
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:23,826
Reo-kun

185
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:25,536
yes

186
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:29,582
(Kyoko) You are everyone's leader, right?

187
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,250
yes

188
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:34,253
(Kyoko) Just because I saw this article all the time⸺

189
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:36,922
Hoihoi, don't trust me

190
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:38,966
Sorry

191
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:40,968
But I am⸺

192
00:12:41,051 --> 00:12:45,598
When I met Erika in the president's office the other day, I thought she was a sincere person.

193
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:50,352
Reo-kun

194
00:12:50,936 --> 00:12:55,191
Can I come to your usual room for a moment?

195
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:59,069
I'll talk about the future

196
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:06,494
There's something I want to talk about seriously with you two.

197
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:18,756
(Masayuki) This time at the space hotel⸺

198
00:13:18,839 --> 00:13:22,259
I would like to talk to you about the attached complex.

199
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:24,929
(Takahashi) I am compiling the materials and will give them to you later.

200
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:26,138
(Employee) Thank you.

201
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:28,098
(Masayuki) Alright Takahashi, I'll just ask you to sort things out one more time.

202
00:13:28,182 --> 00:13:29,391
I got it

203
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:45,825
-(Takahashi) What happened? -(Masayuki) No, it's nothing.

204
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:46,909
Let's go

205
00:13:59,129 --> 00:14:00,548
Juna-chan

206
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,759
(Kina) Yukini!

207
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:08,597
Yaa!

208
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:11,851
Kina-chan, what about your mom?

209
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:12,893
work

210
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:17,815
You know, there was someone who suddenly became unwell.

211
00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:20,651
So I decided to go instead.

212
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:23,445
When we are in trouble, we look to each other, right?

213
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:24,947
I agree

214
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,659
Ah... So Kina-chan, what's for dinner tonight?

215
00:14:28,742 --> 00:14:30,619
There's a chin

216
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:34,790
Even so, you'll be alone until late.

217
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,961
I'll try to contact mom⸺

218
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:41,505
If you don't mind, can I go to Homoho's house with Yukini and I?

219
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:43,257
Yes, let's go!

220
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:45,759
(Yukiya) OK, I'll give you a call.

221
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:46,677
Yeah

222
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:53,475
Oh, hello, are you Kina's mother?

223
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:00,232
Good job

224
00:15:00,899 --> 00:15:01,900
please

225
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,193
thank you

226
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:06,238
-(Yukiya) Is everyone here? -(Girl) Yeah.

227
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:08,616
- (Yukiya) Alright - (Girl) Let's put our hands together.

228
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:12,119
(Children) Itadakimasu

229
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:56,872
(Kyoko) Hey, why?

230
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:04,338
Kyoko, that's not true.

231
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:06,382
What's the difference?

232
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:11,011
You said you'd make me happy, right?

233
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,640
(Reo) That's... I said it.

234
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:16,767
So why?

235
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:25,401
Am I no good at all?

236
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:27,236
(Reo) It's not like that.

237
00:16:28,821 --> 00:16:32,825
There's nothing wrong with having days like this

238
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:44,795
What is this, “Erika-san Erika-san”?

239
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:47,256
What's good about a woman like that?

240
00:16:47,339 --> 00:16:48,757
(Reo) In that way...

241
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:54,096
How much do you think I'm paying you guys?

242
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,432
Yeah? 100 million?

243
00:16:57,141 --> 00:17:02,104
If it weren't for me, you'd be a number you'd never have anything to do with, right?

244
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,862
What is your benefactor?

245
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:17,077
I can't thank you enough, can I?

246
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,456
I...

247
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:24,126
I want to get serious about this business.

248
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:29,423
Kyoko also saw that and agreed with me, right?

249
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:30,883
Yeah, of course

250
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:34,094
“I’m proud to be an investor”⸺

251
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:36,221
You told me, right?

252
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:42,436
What are you talking about?

253
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:46,315
Are you serious?

254
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:54,573
If you want to be a full-fledged person, try entertaining me.

255
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:14,551
Ah~

256
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:58,428
(Kotoko) Sorry for being late.

257
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:01,140
No, not at all, thank you for your hard work.

258
00:19:02,015 --> 00:19:03,475
I was a good girl

259
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:13,861
(Kotoko) I'm sorry, I'm so used to you.

260
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:16,822
Now I often do it at home⸺

261
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:19,199
Saying “Yuki-ni, Yukini”

262
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:28,208
I think this child is happy because she doesn't know her father.

263
